{
  "text": "The representation of rate. Thus far, the coordination of rates has been explained with a simple qualitative formula. This formalization does not provide any mechanism by which this coordination occurs. [CITATION_1] describe a possible mechanism in their account of depictive models. A depictive model is a computer implementation of physical imagery based on the object-oriented paradigm of computer programming. In a depictive model, the primary ontological entity is not a spatial array. Instead, it is an imagined object that includes rate constraints and that sends real-time ''messages'' that indicate its rate of change.",
